    {
      "id": "fac10b2fb0571f04039ed94ffe47a806c4e071ea",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 166,
        "name": "Wally Wang",
        "email": "wang@cray.com",
        "username": "wang",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-09 01:20:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n1. We need the following chunk, in ext4-misc-sles11.patch, in order to get through a compiler warning that start_ext.ee_block may not be initialized. May be we can add it to ext4-misc-rhel6.patch?\n\n--- linux/fs/ext4/move_extent.c\n+++ linux/fs/ext4/move_extent.c\n@@ -483,7 +483,7 @@\n\n\to_start = o_end = oext = orig_path[depth].p_ext;\n\toext_alen = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(oext);\n-\tstart_ext.ee_len = end_ext.ee_len = 0;\n+\tstart_ext.ee_block = start_ext.ee_len = end_ext.ee_len = 0;\n\n\tnew_ext.ee_block = cpu_to_le32(*from);\n\text4_ext_store_pblock(&new_ext, ext_pblock(dext));\n\n2. We might need the barrier patch if performance is till bad: \n    ext4-disable-write-bar-by-default.patch\n    Oracle bug 20205\n\n3. The changes in ext4-include-fixes-2.6-sles11.patch, could you explain where are they from? Wondering if they belong there.\n\nWally",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3e344d8984eb98c344542c156a0f359a183a9097",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 166,
        "name": "Wally Wang",
        "email": "wang@cray.com",
        "username": "wang",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-07-11 16:54:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIs HAVE_BDI_NAME needed for sp0 or sp1?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "12d8b388a0509b68803f1db9032ee1722764f1ce",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-12 15:27:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBDI handling patch is needed for SP0. The script should handling it correctly based on the kernel header.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "31ad65a49d425b860467fe6a2b8eb07af176e942",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-12 15:55:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nPatch Set 3:\n\n1. We need the following chunk, in ext4-misc-sles11.patch, in order to get through a compiler warning that start_ext.ee_block may not be initialized. May be we can add it to ext4-misc-rhel6.patch?\n\nI agree the best place would be ext4-misc-rhel6.patch\n\n--- linux/fs/ext4/move_extent.c +++ linux/fs/ext4/move_extent.c @@ -483,7 +483,7 @@\n\no_start = o_end = oext = orig_path[depth].p_ext;\noext_alen = ext4_ext_get_actual_len(oext);\n- start_ext.ee_len = end_ext.ee_len = 0;\n+ start_ext.ee_block = start_ext.ee_len = end_ext.ee_len = 0;\n\nnew_ext.ee_block = cpu_to_le32(*from);\next4_ext_store_pblock(&new_ext, ext_pblock(dext));\n\n2. We might need the barrier patch if performance is till bad:\next4-disable-write-bar-by-default.patch\nOracle bug 20205\n\nI can send you patch with this fix to compare the results.\n\n3. The changes in ext4-include-fixes-2.6-sles11.patch, could you explain where are they from? Wondering if they belong there.\n\nWhat ext4-include-fixes-2.6-sles11.patch does is alter the SuSE kernel code such that we can reuse all the rhel6 patches instead of redoing them all. The hope is that we can keep in sync easier with any improvements in the rhel6 code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
