      "date": "2011-11-29 23:40:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(3 inline comments)\n\nJames,\nthanks for reviving this patch.  I was just about to ping you on it, since it would be nice to get the SLES11 kernel patches into 2.2, even if we don't have the resources to test it ourselves.\n\nI would like to land this, but the bdev_read_only() patch appears incorrect, and will very likely result in test failures, and possibly even filesystem corruption during failback.  I don't understand why that is needed, since dev_check_rdonly() should exist in the server kernel patches.",
